JOHANNESBURG – The Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University (NMMU) has officially inaugurated former cabinet minister Dr Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi as its new Chancellor. The inauguration took place on Tuesday. Fraser-Moleketi assumed her role as Chancellor on 1 April. WATCH: Mbeki inaugurated as Unisa chancellor She previously served as a Public Service and Administration minister between 1999 and 2008. It is the first local university to appoint three women to head up the institution. Ambassador Nozipho January-Bardill was appointed Chair of Council, with Prof Sibongile Muthwa serving as the Vice-Chancellor. eNCA